The paper deals with the theoretical foundations of neural networks, specifically extending the definition to general topological groups and proving universal approximation theorems. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SI) in the context of approximating functions. Finally, the paper deals with the structure and properties of neural networks, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
